Hello all,

Recently, a package I submitted to Bioconductor failed with an
error message in the OS X system.

This is the link for the build:
http://bioconductor.org/spb_reports/PubScore_buildreport_20191208212325.html#celaya2_buildsrc_anchor

The problem was with the Cairo package, which is a dependency of "plotly":
https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/plotly/index.html


Stack Overflow says that if I owned the Mac, I should install xquartz,
which doesn't come anymore built in the OS X system.

Any suggestions of how I can proceed?
Best and thanks,
Tiago




